message.text:
France: July 4 BEYOND KIMONO - Beauty of Japan 
How would you depict the four seasons with a modern traditional dress? 
A fashion show by vintage Kimono designer Eiko Kobayashi will give you the answer. 

Kimono, literally translated as "a thing to wear" (ki着 "wear" and mono物 "thing"), is mostly worn on special occasions today: on New Year's Day（お正月）, coming‐of‐age ceremony（成人式）, a day of prayer for the healthy growth of young children（七五三）...the decorative colors and beautiful embroidery brightens up every event and makes it more fun and festive！　

フランス：7/4 ファッションショー： BEYOND KIMONO - Beauty of Japan

message.text:
Domo-kun will visit the Japan Foundation in Paris on July 2nd around 12:30 PM!  Come and meet Domo-kun at the Japan Foundation!

Domo-kun is a popular mascot  for NHK, a Japan's national public TV station, and will be in Paris for Japan Expo, one of the largest event on J-POP culture in Europe, to promote NHK World TV! 
By the way, "DOMO（どうも、どーも）" is very convenient casual Japanese word. Do you know how it's used? 
http://www3.nhk.or.jp/nhkworld/domo/index.html 

明後日７月２日（水）、国際交流基金パリ日本文化会館に、あの！NHKのどーもくんがお昼の12時半やってきます！どーもくんは、パリで開催される欧州最大の日本文化の祭典「ジャパンエキスポ」で、NHKWORLDのPRもするそうですよ。
どーもくんの名前の「どうも、どーも」、とっても便利な言葉ですが、どんなときに使うか知っていますか？

Say it Together! Basic Japanese Words in Japanese Alphabetical Order
Today's Word is "Chi" CHIZU #nihongo　#map
日本の単語を五十音順にわかりやすく紹介！「ち」ず
http://words.marugotoweb.jp/search_detail.php?id=1708%2C607&p=1&q=地図&source=search&lang=en

Ａ world map looks different depending where you are, and of course Japanese one puts Japan in its center! How does your map look like?Share it with us!
世界地図はあなたがどこにいるかによって描き方が違います。もちろん日本にある地図は日本が真ん中！あなたの国の地図はどういう地図ですか？あなたの地図、シェアしてください！
